# Wisleess2

**Secure, protocol‚ÄĎagnostic toolkit for building P2P mesh networks over unreliable and reliable transports.**



## Overview

Wisleess2 is a **pure Rust** library that implements all the logic required to build secure, flexible, and censorship‚ÄĎresistant communication protocols. It does **not** handle physical data transmission (sockets, Bluetooth, etc.) ‚Äď you provide the byte transport, and Wisleess2 takes care of the rest.

The crate is:
- **Cross‚ÄĎplatform** ‚Äď no platform‚ÄĎspecific code, no external dependencies.
- **Highly configurable** ‚Äď plug your own crypto, key exchange, nonce generation, CRC, and traffic obfuscation.
- **Memory‚ÄĎsafe** ‚Äď `#![forbid(unsafe_code)]` and strict Clippy lints (no indexing, no unwrapping).
- **Extensively tested** ‚Äď test code is more than twice the size of production code.

## Key features

- **Packet framing & fragmentation** ‚Äď split byte streams into packets and reassemble them, even when the underlying channel reorders, duplicates, or loses data.
- **Pluggable cryptography** ‚Äď support for any stream cipher + authentication tag (AEAD‚ÄĎlike) via simple traits (`EncWis`, `Noncer`, `Cfcser`, `Randomer`, `Thrasher`).
- **Flexible key exchange** ‚Äď implement arbitrary handshake protocols with the `HandMaker` trait.
- **Intelligent queues**:
  - `WSUdpLike` ‚Äď reorder out‚ÄĎof‚ÄĎorder packets and detect gaps.
  - `WSWaitQueue` ‚Äď track unconfirmed packets with configurable timeouts and resend logic.
  - `WSRecvQueueCtrs` ‚Äď batch acknowledgements (fback) to minimise overhead.
  - `WSTcpLike` ‚Äď reconstruct packet boundaries from a continuous byte stream (TCP‚ÄĎstyle).
- **Traffic obfuscation**:
  - Insert randomised ‚Äútrash‚ÄĚ (user) fields at fixed positions.
  - Send fake data and fake fback packets with configurable probabilities.
  - Randomise packet lengths to resist DPI.
- **Header integrity** ‚Äď optional CRC32‚ÄĎlike checksums (pluggable algorithm) for unreliable channels.
- **Time‚ÄĎTo‚ÄĎLive (TTL)** ‚Äď multi‚ÄĎhop packet lifetime control with custom hop cost (positive or negative).
- **Connection multiplexing** ‚Äď separate sessions via `IdConnect` field.
- **Minimal overhead** ‚Äď as low as **18 bytes** (16‚ÄĎbyte authentication tag + 1‚ÄĎbyte counter + 1‚ÄĎbyte control flags). The exact size depends on your topology configuration.
- **No heap allocations in hot paths** ‚Äď many operations use stack‚ÄĎallocated buffers.

## Architecture overview

The library is built around several core concepts:

- **`PackTopology`** ‚Äď describes the layout of a packet header: positions and lengths of all fields (counter, IDs, length, CRC, nonce, TTL, user fields, etc.).  
- **`GroupTopology`** ‚Äď a set of interchangeable topologies selected by a ‚Äútricky byte‚ÄĚ, allowing dynamic packet shapes.
- **`WsConnectParam`** ‚Äď static connection parameters (MTU, timeouts, queue sizes, fake traffic probabilities, etc.).
- **`WsConnection`** ‚Äď the main connection state machine (counters, queues, crypto, handshake, file splitting).
- **`WSFileSplitter`** ‚Äď splits large files into chunks and reassembles them from arbitrary slices.
- **Traits** ‚Äď all algorithms (encryption, nonce generation, CRC, random, user field generation, handshake) are injected via traits, making the library crypto‚ÄĎagnostic.

## Requirements

- Rust **1.70** or later (edition 2021)
- No `std::net`, no async runtime, no external crates ‚Äď pure `core` + `alloc`.

## Status

The library is **~80% complete**. Core functionality is implemented and heavily tested. Remaining work focuses on:
- API polishing
- Final integration of the handshake machinery
- Additional stress tests and documentation examples